From abf0e605b688715e8163b8203a5793064b9403b8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: srtlab <gomezsteve1379@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 23:12:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] KeyProgTab: gate the UNVERIFIED XC2268 SEC16 write (parity
 with ModuleSync/engine)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

KeyProgTab already resolves the BCM secret through the engine resolver
(info.bcmSec16 = resolveBcmSec16, so it inherited the legacy-BCM fix) — no
resolution drift. But runKeyProgPatch and runRfhBcmSync wrote XC2268 RFHUB
SEC16 with the UNVERIFIED writeXc2268Sec16 (offset map + image checksum
reconstructed from a screenshot) with NO acknowledgement — a real 2019+ Ram
RFHUB could be bricked.

Both now refuse the XC2268 write unless allowUnverifiedTarget is passed (same
standard as marryModule and ModuleSync); Gen2 Yazaki stays ungated (bench-
verified). KeyProgTab surfaces an opt-in checkbox when the patcher reports the
UNVERIFIED block. Charger62BenchPanel is Gen2-EEE-specific so the gate never
fires there. CI test covers refuse / acknowledge / Gen2-ungated. esbuild-valid.
